# tabbing-on

## A terminal tab title, status & task manager.
## Works with Ghostty, iTerm2, Kitty, WezTerm, Alacritty, and more.

$ tabbing-on help

# Quick Start

## Set a tab title with color, emoji, and urgency level.

$ tabbing-on "The Great American Novel" -blue "Pick Genre" -rocket

## Check the current state anytime with no arguments.

$ tabbing-on

# Status Updates

## Change status with different emojis — watch the tab title.

$ tabbing-status -brain "Research Train Schedules"

$ tabbing-status -search "Locomotive Black Market"

$ tabbing-status -coffee "Watch the Station Agent"

$ tabbing-status -fire "Write hype blog"

# Urgency Levels

## Urgency 0-5 controls the color. 0 = critical (red), 5 = nominal (gray).

$ tabbing-status -pri0 "DEADLINE TOMORROW"

$ tabbing-on

## Dramatic pivot — new project, red highlight, critical urgency.

$ tabbing-on "Expunge Novel Plans" -red "Holding back tears" -pri0

$ tabbing-on

# Available Emojis

## 47 named emojis covering builds, status, activity, review, infra, and more.

$ tabbing-on emojis

# Available Colors

$ tabbing-on colors

# Todo Management

## Start a real project and add subtasks.

$ tabbing-on "Acme Dashboard" -green "Planning" -gear -pri4

$ tabbing-todo "K8 infra setup" -e gear -m "Deploy to staging cluster"

$ tabbing-todo "UX Design" -e art -m "Figma mockups"

$ tabbing-todo "Style Guide" -e sparkle

$ tabbing-todo "Choose Framework" -e search -p 2

## List all todos for this tab.

$ tabbing-todo

## Pick one to work on. Type a number at the prompt.

$ echo "1" | tabbing-todo --pick

## The tab title now shows the active todo.

$ tabbing-on

## Mark it done.

$ tabbing-todo --done

## Pick the next one.

$ echo "2" | tabbing-todo --pick

$ tabbing-on

# Terminal Detection

## tabbing-on detects your terminal and uses proprietary features where available.

$ tabbing-on --terminal-info

# History & Reporting

## Every title/status change is logged with timestamps.

$ tabbing-history

## Time-in-state report as an ASCII bar chart.

$ tabbing-report

## Same data as Mermaid syntax — paste into GitHub markdown, docs, etc.

$ tabbing-report --mermaid

## Search across all history.

$ tabbing-history "Novel"

# Full Tab Info

## Everything about this tab: state, file paths, recordings, todos.

$ tabbing-info

# Multi-Shell Support

## One-liner init for bash or zsh.

$ bin/tabbing-init --help
